parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Front End Wobble/Steering Head Bearing Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The front end wobble can cause loss of control, accidents, and injuries, especially when decelerating or cornering at high speeds.
symptoms: The front end of the motorcycle wobbles or shakes violently
making it difficult to control the vehicle. The handlebars may pulsate or wobble from left to right
and the motorcycle may pull to one side.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the drive flange bearing can cause the wheel to lock up, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: pieces of flange bearing found on the ground or inside the hub

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear hub bearing can cause the wheel to seize, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially resulting in injury or death.
symptoms: The rear hub bearing is dry due to the lack of a grease seal
the bearing balls have disintegrated and turned blue from excessive heat
the rear tire flange bearings are failed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission problems can cause the vehicle to lose power, hesitate, or suddenly shift into neutral, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potentially resulting in injury or death.
symptoms: The vehicle would not engage into 5th gear
the gear goes into neutral between 4th and 5th gear
the vehicle slams into 4th gear during acceleration.
